                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d20">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.20/743: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-02-13T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >February 13, 1942—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>97. Major General Joseph W. Stilwell is proceeding to Chungking as the head of a
                    military mission to China which will include the functions of the Magruder
                    groups. The War Department has informed General Magruder of the character and
                    functions of the Stilwell mission. Prior to General Stilwell’s arrival you may
                    wish <pb facs="0028" n="18" xml:id="pg_18"/> to obtain from General Magruder
                    further details with regard to the Stilwell mission.</p>
                <p>John Davies, Jr., F.S.O. VII, has been assigned Consul at Kunming, designated
                    Second Secretary at Chungking for temporary duty, and detailed to the Stilwell
                    mission for liaison purposes. He is proceeding promptly, carrying full
                    instructions as to his duties.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
